originalText.text:
The place was crowded with old people. It made everything even more slower because the deals weren't to the customers liking. I suggest that there would be a designated person just for the older generation that doesn't know why they came to the place from the first place. There were some employees that looked like they where in LA LA land and staying in their post, instead of them looking to help someone else.
Also one big mistake that they do here is, when they call the names for the next customer they yell it like 2 times and people can't even hear their names yelled out. If it wasn't for me looking to the side where the monitor had my name I wouldn't have known my name was yelled out.

This is basically like DMV from 125th street. They need a better system.

If it wasn't for the good customer service from Harold I would of given this place 1 star. He was very pleasant to talk to.
